{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-page-js","path":"/projects/british-museum-audio-guide","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In 2015, I joined the Department of Digital and Publishing at the British Museum. The first project\nI was asked to help with, was to create an API for the audio guides endpoint for the public to retrieve\ndetails of their visit.</p>\n<p>The audio guides project had been written to interface with Contentful, but there was no budget to\ncreate the public endpoint, so I was asked to do this. I made a simple API using Zend Framework 2 &#x26;  Apigility\nframework.</p>\n<p>The basic premise behind this project is this:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Customer rents audio guide</li>\n<li>Follows trail around museum listening to audio at different stops</li>\n<li>Returns device, which is cleared and data sent via NFC integration</li>\n<li>This POSTS a JSON data file to the API endpoint</li>\n<li>A personalised webpage is generated and an email is sent to the user for them to view.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The JSON file was very simple:</p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"json\" terminal=\"carbon\"  >\n          <code slot=\"code\">{\n  &quot;email&quot;: &quot;no@email.com&quot;,\n  &quot;locale&quot;: &quot;en&quot;,\n  &quot;started&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:35:52&quot;,\n  &quot;ended&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:56&quot;,\n  &quot;subscribed&quot;: &quot;false&quot;,\n  &quot;stops&quot;: [\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;4ONf3sj0eIE4IcE0E2GwkO&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:35&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;1MQ21QWbVCuyI8uGWuIUei&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;4xwPhFW54cSAaCaYUuWCwu&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;24lu9axfd2QkgcW6c6oYAk&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;22626eTuvqSeO0oWEcm8iA&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;1tn1NOdQzSIYKG0SoAqea8&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;19kfJVj4GUo0Eq48EgoSUO&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;2nvxSuLlJaqAK8qyYWwac0&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;6Wr8NhErvOksagusSoa24k&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;3cCkxzlla0imO2Q68CSmcY&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;3J1Cm7YIIo4oOu2cuoWI0O&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    },\n    {\n      &quot;stop_id&quot;: &quot;60sn0B0XQsGuekigoq0e2y&quot;,\n      &quot;date_visited&quot;: &quot;2015-11-18 11:43:28&quot;\n    }\n  ]\n}</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<p>The contentful stop id, and the date visited. The API then used the stop ID to get further data.</p>\n<p>The page they saw looked like the below:</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 153%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/f1512/myVisitMuseum.webp 200w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/f59aa/myVisitMuseum.webp 400w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/47a22/myVisitMuseum.webp 800w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/5bb53/myVisitMuseum.webp 1200w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/aa619/myVisitMuseum.webp 1400w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/f8f3a/myVisitMuseum.png 200w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/6a8a8/myVisitMuseum.png 400w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/7842b/myVisitMuseum.png 800w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/5ece7/myVisitMuseum.png 1200w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/4af54/myVisitMuseum.png 1400w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/7842b/myVisitMuseum.png\"\n            alt=\"British Museum audio guide API and take away pages\"\n            title=\"British Museum audio guide API and take away pages\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">British Museum audio guide API and take away pages</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The consumer would receive the email in one of the languages that the system supported,\nand the page would be in the same language and present as LTR or RTL depending on the language. They could\nclick on the object and get further details.</p>\n<p>The API allowed <a href=\"https://github.com/portableant/audioGuideExtractorInRstats\">simple analytics</a> to be done via R stats\nusing a MYSQL connection.</p>\n<h2>How did the tech work at the back end?</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>NFC tag read by the returning desk</li>\n<li>Data sent to the API as a JSON file</li>\n<li>API saves the data to a database</li>\n<li>Web page would pull data from Contentful system and present the web page</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The project's code has been deleted from the Github repository I set up for the BM, but the code\nis available via Zenodod and on my personal repository account.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"October 29, 2019","section":"projects","title":"British Museum audio guide API and take away pages","role":"API Developer","featuredImg":{"id":"cfbc578b-5f5a-55db-a7c1-caeafa37bc50","absolutePath":"/Users/danielpett/Documents/GitHub/museologi.st/images/2017/myVisitMuseum.png","publicURL":"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/myVisitMuseum.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/e0d94/myVisitMuseum.png","srcSet":"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/61e45/myVisitMuseum.png 150w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/a6169/myVisitMuseum.png 300w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/e0d94/myVisitMuseum.png 600w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/6e49c/myVisitMuseum.png 1200w","sizes":"(min-width: 600px) 600px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/1fbbf/myVisitMuseum.avif 150w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/11d3f/myVisitMuseum.avif 300w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/3aa78/myVisitMuseum.avif 600w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/ec59f/myVisitMuseum.avif 1200w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 600px) 600px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/4357c/myVisitMuseum.webp 150w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/094cc/myVisitMuseum.webp 300w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/88988/myVisitMuseum.webp 600w,\n/static/2c801274a402fa5e86017acfc99f90c2/1ccf0/myVisitMuseum.webp 120